# Structure Consistency

Keep the repo structure simple and consistent when adding or refactoring files.

## App Components

- In `src/components/app/`, keep single-file pages directly under `app/`
- Only create a page subfolder when the page has supporting components or related files that belong beside it
- If a formerly single-file page grows support files later, it is fine to introduce a dedicated folder then

## UI Components

- In `src/components/ui/`, files whose main export is a React component should use `PascalCase.tsx`
- Use lowercase-style naming only for non-component helper modules

## Imports And Cleanup

- Prefer local imports without explicit `.ts` or `.tsx` extensions
- Remove empty folders, stale paths, and stray system files such as `.DS_Store` when making structural changes
- Before adding local helpers, wrappers, or type shims, check whether an installed dependency already provides the needed primitive and prefer that when it fits
